<!-- ============= Usage ============================= -->
  <sect1 id="gcalc-usage"> 
	 <title>Usage</title> 
	 
	 <sect2 id="gcalc-basic-functions"> 
		<title>To Use Basic Calculator Functions</title> 
		<para>To perform a basic calculation, use one of the following
		  methods:</para> 
		<itemizedlist> 
		  <listitem> 
			 <para>Click on the calculator buttons to enter numbers and
				mathematical functions.</para> 
		  </listitem> 
		  <listitem> 
			 <para>Give focus to the <application>&app;</application>, then use
				the numeric keypad to specify the mathematical calculation you want to
				perform.</para> 
		  </listitem> 
		</itemizedlist> 
		<para>The numbers that you enter and the results of calculations are
		  displayed in the display field. If you enter an incorrect number, click 
		  <guibutton>C/CE</guibutton> to delete the number, then reenter the correct
		  number.</para> 
		<para>To copy the result of a calculation, choose 
		  <menuchoice> 
			 <guimenu>Edit</guimenu> 
			 <guimenuitem>Copy</guimenuitem> 
		  </menuchoice>. You can paste the value into another application.</para>
		
		<para>To clear the result of a calculation, perform one of the following
		  actions: </para> 
		<itemizedlist> 
		  <listitem> 
			 <para>Click <guibutton>AC</guibutton> to clear the result of a
				calculation from the memory buffer and from the display field.</para> 
		  </listitem> 
		  <listitem> 
			 <para>Click <guibutton>C/CE</guibutton> to clear the result of a
				calculation from the display field.</para> 
		  </listitem> 
		</itemizedlist> 
		<para><application>&app;</application> automatically displays large
		  integer numbers and small decimal numbers as exponential numbers. For example,
		  if you use <application>&app;</application> to multiply 1200000 by 100000, the
		  calculator displays the result as 1.2e+11. This result signifies 1.2 multiplied
		  by 10 to the power of 11. If you enter the number 0.00001, the calculator
		  displays the number as 1e-05, which signifies 1 multiplied by 10 to the power
		  of -5. For information about how to enter a number in exponential format, see
		  <xref linkend="gcalc-exp-numbers"/>. </para> 
	 </sect2> 
