<!-- ============= Technical Information ============================= -->
  <sect1 id="gcalc-tech-info"> 
	 <title>Technical Information</title> 
	 <sect2 id="gcalc-manage-order"> 
		<title>Order of Operations</title> 
		<para><application>&app;</application> performs calculations in the
		  following order:</para> 
		<orderedlist> 
		  <listitem> 
			 <para>Calculations enclosed in parentheses.</para> 
		  </listitem> 
		  <listitem> 
			 <para>Functions that take a single value, for example +/-, log, x!,
				or SQRT. </para> 
		  </listitem> 
		  <listitem> 
			 <para>x^y</para> 
		  </listitem> 
		  <listitem> 
			 <para>*, /</para> 
		  </listitem> 
		  <listitem> 
			 <para>+, -</para> 
		  </listitem> 
		</orderedlist> 
		<para>The following examples illustrate the order in which the calculator
		  performs calculations:</para> 
		<itemizedlist> 
		  <listitem> 
			 <para> <guibutton>(</guibutton>10 <guibutton>+</guibutton> 20 
				<guibutton>)</guibutton> <guibutton>*</guibutton> 6 <guibutton>=</guibutton>
				180</para> 
		  </listitem> 
		  <listitem> 
			 <para>10 <guibutton>+</guibutton> 20 <guibutton>*</guibutton> 6 
				<guibutton>=</guibutton> 130</para> 
		  </listitem> 
		  <listitem> 
			 <para>2 <guibutton>x^y</guibutton> 3 <guibutton>+</guibutton> 2 
				<guibutton>=</guibutton> 10</para> 
		  </listitem> 
		  <listitem> 
			 <para>2 <guibutton>x^y</guibutton> <guibutton>(</guibutton>3 
				<guibutton>+</guibutton> 2 <guibutton>)</guibutton> <guibutton>=</guibutton>
				32</para> 
		  </listitem> 
		</itemizedlist> 
	 </sect2> 
	 <sect2 id="gcalc-precision"> 
		<title>Internal Precision</title> 
		<para><application>&app;</application> uses double floating point
		  precision.</para> 
	 </sect2> 
	 <sect2 id="gcalc-recognize-error"> 
		<title>Error Conditions</title> 
		<para>If you perform an invalid calculation, the calculator displays an e
		  symbol in the display field to indicate an error. For example, if you try to
		  calculate the log of a negative number, the calculator displays the e symbol.
		  To clear the error, click <guibutton>C/CE</guibutton> or 
		  <guibutton>AC</guibutton>.</para> 
